  "original_title": "Australia extends $ 25 m more as humanitarian assistance",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Australia extends $ 25 m more as humanitarian assistance",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Australian Government yesterday said it would provide an additional $ 25 million to help Sri Lanka meet urgent food and healthcare needs as it confronts its worst economic crisis in 70 years.",
        "\u201cDuring this challenging period, Australia stands with the people of Sri Lanka, especially those experiencing severe hardship,\u201d a statement issued by the Australian High Commission said.",
        "The additional support brings Australia\u2019s Official Development Assistance response to $ 75 million. \u201cOur support will be delivered through UN agencies to provide food, health and nutrition services, access to safe water and essential support for those at risk, including women and children,\u201d the statement said.",
        "\u201cAustralia\u2019s continued assistance to Sri Lanka supports our mutual interest in a secure and resilient Indian Ocean and reinforces our 75-year-strong relationship built on cooperation and community connection,\u201d it added.",
        "The extra humanitarian assistance is in addition to the $ 23 million in ongoing development assistance to Sri Lanka in 2022-23 from Australia."
      ],
